A CRIME OF PASSION.

06:41.067 --> 06:43.034
    YES, SIR.
                AGENT HOTCHNER?

06:43.036 --> 06:45.036
            HI, HOW ARE YOU?
    THIS IS AGENT JAREAU.

06:45.038 --> 06:48.974
        SINCE YOU SAID A SPREE
        KILLER MAY BE AT WORK.

06:48.976 --> 06:50.542
    ANY ACTIVITY
    SINCE THE KILLINGS?

06:50.544 --> 06:51.977
        NO, BUT WE JUST SPOKE TO
        A FRIEND OF THE COUPLE

06:51.979 --> 06:54.079
        WHO WAS AT A MARRIAGE
        COUNSELING RETREAT
        WITH THEM.

06:54.081 --> 06:56.014
            THE WIFE
            WASN'T FEELING WELL,

06:56.016 --> 06:59.818
MAYBE THEY SURPRISED THE UNSUB.
WHO REPORTED THE CRIME?

06:59.820 --> 07:01.153
        THE NEIGHBOR
        FROM ACROSS THE STREET.

07:01.155 --> 07:04.656
        ONLY THE SOUND OF A CAR
        BACKFIRING AROUND 2 A.M.

07:04.658 --> 07:07.659
ALL RIGHT,
I'LL LET THE OTHERS KNOW.

07:07.661 --> 07:09.494
                        GOOD.

07:13.533 --> 07:19.104
    Rossi: THIS NEIGHBORHOOD'S
    NOT EXACTLY
    A HIGH TRAFFIC AREA.

07:19.106 --> 07:21.540
THERE'S NO SURVEILLANCE
CAMERAS.

07:21.542 --> 07:22.774
BUT THEY HAVE
AN ARMED GUARD.

07:22.776 --> 07:24.609
WHAT KIND OF PLACE
NEEDS PRIVACY AND SECURITY?

07:24.611 --> 07:26.945
        WELL, IT'S MAINLY
        ATTORNEYS, ACCOUNTANTS,
        PSYCHOLOGISTS.

07:26.947 --> 07:33.018
        MAYBE THEY WERE WORRIED
        ABOUT UNSTABLE PATIENTS
        AND CLIENTS.

07:33.754 --> 07:38.056
            THOSE HAVE TO BE
            THE UNSUB'S BLOODY
            SHOE PRINTS.

07:38.058 --> 07:41.092
YEAH, BUT THERE'S TWO SETS.

07:42.929 --> 07:46.965
    WELL, THE GUARD DIDN'T
    MAKE IT FAR FROM HIS DESK.

07:46.967 --> 07:47.866
            [CAMERA CLICKING]

07:47.868 --> 07:51.069
IT LOOKS LIKE THAT SECOND
SET OF PRINTS STAYED
OUT THERE BY THE EDGE.

07:51.071 --> 07:52.704
            MAYBE HE WAS
            JUST A WITNESS.
            THE UNSUB

07:52.706 --> 07:55.173
            COULD HAVE BEEN
            SURPRISED BY SOMEONE
            ELSE IN THE LOBBY.

07:55.175 --> 07:56.875
MAYBE HE KIDNAPPED THE WITNESS.

07:56.877 --> 07:58.777
        BUT A POSSIBILITY IS
        IT WAS A PARTNER.

07:58.779 --> 08:03.048
    IT WOULD MAKE IT
    A HELL OF A LOT EASIER
    TO OVERTAKE AN ARMED GUARD.

08:03.050 --> 08:04.483
EVEN WITHOUT
GAMBLING PROBLEMS,

08:04.485 --> 08:06.751
I CAN SEE HOW THEY
MAXED OUT 4 CREDIT CARDS.

08:06.753 --> 08:08.987
        SOMETHING VALUABLE
        COULD HAVE BEEN STOLEN

08:08.989 --> 08:12.090
        AND THE POLICE WOULDN'T
        NECESSARILY KNOW.

08:12.092 --> 08:15.760
STATE OF THE ART.
WE SHOULD CHECK
THEIR INSURANCE LIST.

08:15.762 --> 08:16.962
            THE COUPLE WAS FOUND
            OVER HERE.

08:16.964 --> 08:18.864
            THEY WERE BOTH
            SHOT IN THE CHEST.

08:18.866 --> 08:24.169
        WHICH MEANS THE UNSUB
        WAS STANDING
        RIGHT ABOUT HERE.

08:24.171 --> 08:26.771
        HE CAME IN
        FROM THE BACKYARD.

08:30.776 --> 08:33.245
WELL, TALK ABOUT
A BAD GOPHER PROBLEM.

08:33.246 --> 08:35.145
    THESE HOLES WERE DUG
    RECENTLY. LOOK AT THE DIRT.

08:35.148 --> 08:37.082
        WHAT WERE THEY DIGGING
        FOR, BURIED TREASURE?

08:37.083 --> 08:38.917
WHY WOULD THE MYERSONS
BURY ANYTHING IN THEIR YARD,

08:38.919 --> 08:40.684
JUDGING BY THE SAFE
IN THEIR HOUSE?

08:40.687 --> 08:42.020
            SO IT HAD TO BE
            THE UNSUB.

08:42.022 --> 08:44.556
            GOT SURPRISED
            WHEN THEY
            CAME HOME EARLY.

08:44.558 --> 08:48.093
SPENT ANOTHER HOUR
TRYING TO FIND WHAT
HE WAS LOOKING FOR.

08:48.095 --> 08:51.129
            HOW DID HE KNOW
            THERE WAS SOMETHING
            BURIED BACK HERE?

08:51.131 --> 08:53.765
WE'VE BEEN SAYING THIS CRIME
FELT PERSONAL.

08:53.767 --> 08:57.602
WE SHOULD HAVE GARCIA
PULL A LIST
OF PRIOR RESIDENTS.

08:57.604 --> 09:00.805
        THE UNSUB EITHER
        HAS EITHER A PARTNER
        OR A HOSTAGE WITH HIM,

09:00.807 --> 09:02.874
            MOST LIKELY MALE
            BASED ON THE PRINTS.

09:02.876 --> 09:06.111
I DID A SEARCH
OF PREVIOUS OWNERS
OF 23 CHERRY LANE,

09:06.113 --> 09:08.780
AKA, THE MYERSON HOME,
AND BEFORE THEY LIVED THERE,

09:08.782 --> 09:11.116
IT WAS OWNED BY
PROFESSOR HAROLD MASON.

09:11.118 --> 09:14.886
BOUGHT IT FROM THE BANK
WHO REPOSSESSED IT

09:14.888 --> 09:16.121
FROM AMELIA PORTER,

09:16.123 --> 09:18.623
A NOTORIOUS KILLER
IN THE STATE.

09:18.625 --> 09:20.125
        I REMEMBER THAT NAME.

09:20.127 --> 09:22.127
        SHE WAS A 30-YEAR-OLD
        WOMAN.

09:22.129 --> 09:24.162
        SHE AND HER MUCH YOUNGER
        LOVER GOT HIGH ON DRUGS

09:24.164 --> 09:26.164
        AND RAPED AND MURDERED
        HIS SISTER.

09:26.166 --> 09:27.899
            I THINK HER NAME
            WAS MIRIAM.

09:27.901 --> 09:29.200
THE YOUNGER LOVER
WAS BENTON FARLAND,

09:29.202 --> 09:31.803
17 AT THE TIME,
CONVICTED OF MURDER
FOR THE CRIME,

09:31.805 --> 09:34.306
BUT AMELIA FLED THE SCENE.
SHE WASN'T FOUND.

09:34.308 --> 09:39.044
UH, HE SERVED 12 YEARS
AT UTAH STATE PRISON.

09:39.046 --> 09:41.279
AND HE WAS RELEASED
TWO DAYS AGO.

09:41.281 --> 09:42.948
        HE'S GOTTA BE OUR UNSUB.

09:42.950 --> 09:44.783
THANKS, GARCIA.

09:45.151 --> 09:47.285
                    HERE.

09:52.125 --> 09:57.228
    I DON'T THINK SHE WOULD HAVE
    LASTED MUCH LONGER.

10:01.268 --> 10:07.272
            I JUST CAN'T BELIEVE
            HOW MUCH SHE LOOKS
            LIKE MIRIAM.

10:08.240 --> 10:09.207
    MY MOM.

10:09.209 --> 10:12.210
            I DIDN'T KILL HER,
            YOU KNOW.

10:12.212 --> 10:14.079
            I MEAN, I WAS THERE.

10:14.081 --> 10:18.049
        I SHOULD HAVE
        STOPPED AMELIA,
        BUT I DIDN'T KILL HER.

10:18.051 --> 10:19.951
YOU'RE A LIAR!

10:19.953 --> 10:23.955
            I GOT BLAMED 'CAUSE
            AMELIA RAN AWAY.

10:23.957 --> 10:26.791
            BUT I DIDN'T DO IT.

10:27.126 --> 10:29.828
                I LOVED MIRIAM.

10:29.830 --> 10:31.997
            SHE WAS
            EVERYTHING TO ME.

10:31.999 --> 10:35.700
WE DON'T REMEMBER HER
THAT MUCH.

10:35.702 --> 10:38.169
 WE WERE BOTH PRETTY YOUNG.

10:38.171 --> 10:41.906
                WELL, I'M SORRY
                ABOUT THAT.

10:41.908 --> 10:46.277
        I'M SORRY THAT YOU DON'T
        EVEN HAVE MEMORIES.

10:48.114 --> 10:51.182
    SO WHERE ARE WE GONNA HIDE?

10:51.184 --> 10:52.283
    COME ON, THINK ABOUT IT.

10:52.285 --> 10:54.319
    YOU NEED A PLACE
    WHERE YOU'RE SAFE

10:54.321 --> 10:57.722
    AND YOU CAN COME UP
    WITH A PLAN.

10:58.290 --> 11:00.825
                I DON'T KNOW.

11:00.827 --> 11:05.263
    WHO HAS A CABIN
    IN THE MOUNTAINS
    NOT FAR FROM PARK CITY.

11:05.265 --> 11:07.232
        YOUR BUDDY HAS A CABIN?

11:07.234 --> 11:09.167
HIS PARENTS DO.
IT'S LIKE A VACATION HOUSE.

11:09.169 --> 11:11.202
THEY ONLY USE IT A FEW
TIMES OUT OF THE YEAR.

11:11.204 --> 11:13.171
 THE REST OF THE TIME
 IT'S EMPTY.

11:13.173 --> 11:16.374
        WE'LL GO THERE TONIGHT.

11:23.049 --> 11:26.284
        ALL RIGHT, COPY THAT,
        ROSSI. WE'LL GO TALK
        TO BENTON'S FATHER.

11:26.286 --> 11:30.288
WAS A 29-YEAR-OLD
SINGLE MOM OF TWO YOUNG KIDS
WHEN WHEN WAS KILLED.

11:30.290 --> 11:33.258
    HOW DID BENTON
    ONLY SERVE 12 YEARS
    FOR SUCH A HEINOUS CRIME?

11:33.260 --> 11:36.194
WELL, IT WAS A COMBINATION
OF HIS AGE AND WILLINGNESS

11:36.196 --> 11:37.829
TO TESTIFY AGAINST
AMELIA PORTER.

11:37.831 --> 11:39.397
ULTIMATELY THE JURY FELT
HE WAS A SENSITIVE BOY

11:39.399 --> 11:41.800
WHO WAS UNDULY INFLUENCED
BY AN OLDER DOMINANT WOMAN.

11:41.802 --> 11:43.334
            HOW DID AMELIA
            MANAGE TO ESCAPE?

11:43.336 --> 11:45.937
SHE FLED INTO THE WILDERNESS.
HER FATHER WAS A SURVIVALIST,

11:45.939 --> 11:47.772
SO SHE LEARNED
OUTDOOR SKILLS FROM HIM.

11:47.774 --> 11:49.274
    HAS ANYONE SEEN HER
    SINCE THEN?

11:49.276 --> 11:51.076
        THAT'S A GOOD QUESTION.

11:51.078 --> 11:56.281
    HEY, MAMA, ANY CONFIRMED
    SIGHTINGS OF AMELIA PORTER

11:56.283 --> 11:58.717
UH...
        IN THE LAST 12 YEARS?

11:58.719 --> 12:01.252
YEAH. ONE 10 YEARS AGO.

12:01.254 --> 12:03.354
OH. AND ONE 5 YEARS AGO.

12:03.356 --> 12:05.256
BOTH IN CANADA.
ONE IN VANCOUVER,

12:05.258 --> 12:07.025
THE LATEST ONE
IN THE NORTHERN TERRITORIES.

12:07.027 --> 12:09.494
BUT WHEN AUTHORITIES GOT THERE,
SHE WAS NOWHERE TO BE FOUND.

12:09.496 --> 12:11.362
    THE NORTHWEST TERRITORIES
    ARE HARD TO GET TO

12:11.364 --> 12:14.332
ASSUMING BENTON HAS
A MALE PARTNER WITH HIM,

12:14.334 --> 12:17.368
DOES HE HAVE ANY OLD FRIENDS
HERE HE COULD HAVE
RECONNECTED WITH?

12:17.370 --> 12:19.437
UH-UH. WHEN HE WAS A TEEN,
HE WAS A TOTAL LONER.

12:19.439 --> 12:21.206
THAT'S PROBABLY THE REASON
WHY AMELIA PORTER

12:21.208 --> 12:27.112
        ALL RIGHT, WE NEED
        TO LOOK FOR CONNECTIONS
        HE MAY HAVE HAD IN JAIL.

12:36.255 --> 12:40.892
    HEADS UP, GUYS, I GOT
    A REAL BAD FEELING
    ABOUT THIS.

12:53.038 --> 12:55.540
        CLEAR!

12:56.976 --> 12:58.042
                    JJ: CLEAR.

12:58.044 --> 13:00.411
Morgan: GUYS, OVER HERE.

13:04.483 --> 13:07.519
    THE VICTIM IS BENTON'S
    FATHER, OREN FARLAND.

13:07.521 --> 13:09.454
YOU KNOW, THIS COULD
HAVE BEEN THE FIRST KILL,

13:09.456 --> 13:12.957
        OREN LIVED HERE
        WITH HIS GRANDCHILDREN,
        ANDY AND REBECCA.

13:12.959 --> 13:16.027
ARE THESE THE KIDS OF
THE SISTER WHO GOT MURDERED?

13:16.029 --> 13:23.968
IMAGINE YOU'RE
INCARCERATED FOR 12 YEARS
AND HAVE JUST BEEN RELEASED.

13:23.970 --> 13:25.303
WHERE DO YOU GO?

13:25.305 --> 13:29.340
    Reid: YOU HAVE $40 LEFT
    AFTER BUYING A BUS TICKET

13:29.342 --> 13:34.179
    YOU HAVE NO SKILLS
    TO HELP YOU SURVIVE
    IN THE REAL WORLD,

13:34.181 --> 13:38.483
    NO FRIENDS,
    NOWHERE TO TURN BUT FAMILY.

13:41.487 --> 13:43.555
    WHO KNOWS HOW THEY'LL FEEL
    ABOUT SEEING YOU AGAIN,

13:43.557 --> 13:47.559
    BUT, REALLY,
    WHAT CHOICE DO YOU HAVE?

13:48.494 --> 13:50.395
            LOOKS LIKE SOMEONE
            WAS ENTERTAINING.

13:50.397 --> 13:53.198
I THINK IT WAS THE KIDS.

13:58.337 --> 14:01.272
        THANKS FOR THE LEMONADE.

14:01.274 --> 14:03.107
YEAH, SURE.

14:03.109 --> 14:06.578
GRANDPA'S JUST OUT
BUYING SOME GROCERIES. SO...

14:06.580 --> 14:11.082
                YEAH, YOU SAID.

14:16.121 --> 14:21.326
    SO, IS OLD MR. LITVAK
    STILL TEACHING ENGLISH LIT?

14:21.328 --> 14:24.295
            MAN, THAT GUY
            WAS A BALL-BUSTER.

14:24.297 --> 14:29.000
            BUT I PRACTICALLY
            MEMORIZED "MACBETH"
            BECAUSE OF HIM.

14:29.902 --> 14:38.443
    "WILL ALL GREAT NEPTUNE'S
    OCEAN WASH THIS BLOOD CLEAN
    FROM MY HAND?"

14:40.145 --> 14:43.181
    [DOOR OPENS]

14:45.452 --> 14:51.556
I COULD USE A LITTLE HELP
UNLOADING THE GROCERIES.

14:53.926 --> 14:56.027
                HI, DAD.

14:57.997 --> 14:59.230
        THE KIDS SAT HERE.

14:59.232 --> 15:00.531
        OREN SAT AT THE HEAD
        OF THE TABLE,

15:00.533 --> 15:02.200
        WHICH MEANS BENTON
        SAT RIGHT THERE.

15:02.202 --> 15:04.002
BENTON WASN'T SITTING
VERY CLOSE TO OREN,

15:04.004 --> 15:06.104
WHICH MEANS HE WASN'T
EXACTLY WELCOME.

15:06.106 --> 15:09.107
PROBABLY TO APPEASE HIM,
SO HE'D GO AWAY PEACEFULLY

15:09.109 --> 15:10.208
    AND LEAVE THEM ALONE.

15:10.210 --> 15:12.243
THAT OBVIOUSLY DIDN'T HAPPEN.

15:12.245 --> 15:14.412
SO WHAT WENT WRONG?

15:20.486 --> 15:22.453
I JUST WANT TO SAY THANK YOU

15:22.455 --> 15:25.623
FOR LETTING ME STAY
FOR DINNER.

15:26.058 --> 15:28.259
                EAT UP.

15:28.261 --> 15:29.627
                THEN GO.

15:29.629 --> 15:31.930
DAD, IF YOU'D JUST
GIVE ME A SECOND--

15:31.932 --> 15:34.198
            I DON'T HAVE
            ANY CHILDREN LEFT.

15:34.200 --> 15:36.434
IF YOU'D JUST LET ME
EXPLAIN SOMETHING.

15:36.436 --> 15:37.602
            I'M NOT INTERESTED.

15:37.604 --> 15:38.436
DR. PELMAN SAID

15:38.438 --> 15:39.938
    THAT IF WE DON'T FORGIVE,

15:39.940 --> 15:41.606
        WE'LL NEVER HEAL
        AND MOVE ON.

15:41.608 --> 15:47.512
IS THAT THE B.S.
I PAY THAT QUACK
THERAPIST TO TELL YOU?

15:47.514 --> 15:50.515
"THEN YOU WILL REMEMBER
YOUR EVIL WAYS

15:50.517 --> 15:52.984
"AND YOUR DEEDS
THAT WERE NOT GOOD.

15:52.986 --> 15:55.586
"AND YOU WILL LOATHE
YOURSELVES IN YOUR OWN SIGHT

15:55.588 --> 16:01.960
FOR YOUR INIQUITIES
AND YOUR ABOMINATIONS."

16:01.962 --> 16:07.065
    YOU SHOW UP LIKE A BAD PENNY
    TO QUOTE SCRIPTURE TO ME?

16:07.067 --> 16:14.072
AND I WOULD KILL MYSELF
RIGHT NOW IF IT WOULD
BRING MIRIAM BACK.

16:15.007 --> 16:17.241
    MAYBE IT WILL.

16:17.643 --> 16:20.578
    YOU SHOULD GIVE IT A TRY.

16:31.457 --> 16:35.360
I KNOW YOU'LL NEVER
FORGIVE ME.

16:35.362 --> 16:37.762
BUT I'M YOUR OWN
FLESH AND BLOOD.

16:37.764 --> 16:41.599
DON'T YOU HAVE ANY FEELINGS
FOR ME AT ALL?

16:49.541 --> 16:54.712
        THE FEELING I HAVE
        FOR YOU FOR YOU IS...

16:55.581 --> 16:57.615
            I'D LIKE TO GUT YOU

16:57.617 --> 16:59.617
        FOR BEING THE VILE
        BASTARD THAT YOU ARE!

16:59.619 --> 17:01.452
                Andy: GRANDPA!
                STOP!

17:01.454 --> 17:04.055
    Reid: OREN COULDN'T
    CONTAIN IS ANGER.

17:04.057 --> 17:05.522
    HE STOOD UP,
    THREATENED BENTON,

17:05.525 --> 17:08.626
    WHO THEN STABBED HIM
    WITH THE STEAK KNIFE.

17:11.163 --> 17:14.298
I THINK I KNOW WHAT
HAPPENED TO THE KIDS.

17:14.300 --> 17:15.633
                    AAH! OHH!

17:15.635 --> 17:18.669
                        OHH!

17:20.506 --> 17:21.705
 NO! NO!

17:21.708 --> 17:23.374
NO, NO, NO!
NO, LET HER GO!

17:23.376 --> 17:24.608
        YOU SAW WHAT
        HE WAS GONNA DO.

17:24.611 --> 17:26.109
    HE WAS TRYING TO KILL ME.
    I HAD NO CHOICE!

17:26.112 --> 17:28.279
THAT'S WHAT WE'RE
GONNA TELL THE COPS.

17:28.281 --> 17:33.317
I JUST GOT OUT OF PRISON.
THEY'LL THROW ME BACK
IN THERE FOR LIFE!

17:33.319 --> 17:35.286
    OK. LOOK,
    WE WON'T CALL THEM.

17:35.288 --> 17:38.523
I GOT A BETTER IDEA.
YOU'RE BOTH COMING WITH ME.

17:38.525 --> 17:41.692
    BENTON PROBABLY
    TOOK THE KIDS
    AS AN INSURANCE POLICY.

17:41.694 --> 17:44.162
        HE KNEW THE POLICE
        WOULDN'T BELIEVE HIM,

17:44.164 --> 17:46.631
    [CELL PHONE RINGS]
        HEY, WHAT YOU GOT,
        BABY GIRL?

17:46.633 --> 17:48.666
I'VE CONFIRMED
IT WASN'T A RANDOM THING

17:48.668 --> 17:51.169
THAT BENTON FARLAND
SHOWED UP AT THAT OFFICE

17:51.171 --> 17:52.737
WHERE THE SECURITY GUARD
WAS KILLED,

17:52.739 --> 17:55.306
BECAUSE ANDY FARLAND
HAS A THERAPIST

17:55.308 --> 17:57.442
NAMED DR. PELMAN
WHO WORKS THERE.

17:57.444 --> 17:58.709
            HOW LONG WAS ANDY
            IN THERAPY?

17:58.711 --> 18:00.578
UH, 3 YEARS. HE WAS
HAVING TROUBLE IN SCHOOL.

18:00.580 --> 18:04.649
    THAT'S NOT A SURPRISE
    GIVEN HIS MOTHER WAS
    MURDERED BY HIS UNCLE.

18:04.651 --> 18:06.751
        GARCIA, DID ANDY
        HAVE ANY CONTACT
        WITH BENTON

18:06.753 --> 18:07.718
        WHEN HE WAS IN PRISON?

18:07.720 --> 18:09.253
UH-HUH. UNFORTUNATELY, YES.

18:09.255 --> 18:12.156
ALL OF IT THE LAST TWO YEARS.
HE VISITED HIM TWICE,

18:12.158 --> 18:15.593
        CONTACT WITH BENTON
        MAY HAVE HUMANIZED HIM.

18:15.595 --> 18:20.131
        INSTEAD OF FEARING HIM,
        ANDY MIGHT ACTUALLY
        HAVE EMPATHY FOR HIM.

18:28.307 --> 18:32.176
IF YOU BEHAVE...

18:32.178 --> 18:36.114
I PROMISE
I WON'T HURT YOU.

18:36.116 --> 18:38.149
DO YOU BELIEVE ME?

18:38.151 --> 18:41.219
DO YOU BELIEVE ME?

18:42.754 --> 18:46.424
YOU KNOW, WHEN I WAS LITTLE,

18:46.426 --> 18:51.162
A TEACHER TOLD ME
THAT I WAS SNAKE-BITTEN.

18:51.164 --> 18:53.564
YOU KNOW WHAT THAT MEANS?

18:54.900 --> 18:58.369
I ATTRACT BAD LUCK.

18:58.371 --> 19:00.404
EVERYTHING I TOUCH

19:00.406 --> 19:03.608
TURNS TO GARBAGE.

19:06.245 --> 19:08.813
BUT IT'S NOT MY FAULT.

19:08.815 --> 19:11.149
I'M JINXED.

19:11.151 --> 19:14.185
NOTHING EVER GOES MY WAY.

19:14.187 --> 19:18.356
        YOU FOUND THE MONEY,
        THOUGH, RIGHT?

19:18.358 --> 19:21.325
        IN THE BACKYARD?

19:21.327 --> 19:22.793
YEAH.

19:22.795 --> 19:25.530
I FOUND THE MONEY.

19:25.532 --> 19:26.330
        [SIREN]

19:26.332 --> 19:30.201
            CRAP. WHAT DO I DO?

19:30.203 --> 19:32.236
PULL OVER.

19:58.263 --> 20:00.665
    LICENSE AND REGISTRATION.

20:01.233 --> 20:04.435
    YEAH. IS THERE
    A PROBLEM, OFFICER?

20:04.437 --> 20:07.805
Police radio: WE HAVE A 10-57
WITH MULTIPLE INJURIES

20:07.807 --> 20:10.675
    ALL UNITS IN THE AREA
    PLEASE REPORT.

20:10.677 --> 20:13.611
        COPY THAT.
        VICTOR 5 ON THE WAY.

20:13.613 --> 20:14.845
                10-4, VICTOR 5.

20:14.847 --> 20:18.916
        I'M LETTING YOU OFF
        WITH A WARNING,
        BUT GET IT FIXED.

20:18.918 --> 20:21.252
SURE THING.

20:27.960 --> 20:31.562
MAYBE YOU KIDS
ARE MY LUCKY CHARM.

20:31.564 --> 20:37.368
    BENTON FARLAND WENT HOME
    AND MURDERED HIS FATHER
    IN AN IMPROVISED WAY.

20:37.370 --> 20:41.672
        HE NEEDED A WEAPON,
        SO HE KILLED
        AN ARMED SECURITY GUARD.

20:41.674 --> 20:43.441
        HE THEN WENT OVER
        TO THE MYERSON HOUSE
        TO DIG UP MONEY

20:43.443 --> 20:46.944
        THAT WAS BURIED THERE.
        HE SHOT THE COUPLE
        WHEN THEY SURPRISED HIM.

20:46.946 --> 20:49.880
HE BELIEVES THAT HIS ONLY
CHOICES ARE FIGHT OR FLIGHT.

20:49.882 --> 20:52.650
    Kate: HE'S LOOKING FOR
    ANY WAY HE CAN TO ESCAPE,

20:52.652 --> 20:57.888
JJ: HE'S ARMED AND DANGEROUS
AND HE'S ALREADY KILLED
4 VICTIMS.

20:57.890 --> 21:00.725
        Reid: BENTON IS MOST
        LIKELY TRAVELING

21:00.727 --> 21:06.030
        IT'S A 1993 GOLD VOLVO,
        LICENSE PLATE NUMBER
        631 ZFG.

21:06.032 --> 21:09.900
WE BELIEVE HE'S WITH
HIS NIECE AND NEPHEW,
ANDY AND REBECCA.

21:09.902 --> 21:11.402
    ANDY COULD BE TRYING
    TO HELP HIS UNCLE,

21:11.404 --> 21:14.839
        OR IT COULD BE THAT
        ANDY IS SIMPLY TRYING
        TO PROTECT HIS SISTER.

21:14.841 --> 21:17.975
    YOU NEED TO INCREASE
    PATROLS ON MAJOR ROADS
    LEADING OUT OF THE CITY.

21:17.977 --> 21:21.879
WE CANNOT EMPHASIZE ENOUGH
HOW VOLATILE THIS SITUATION IS.

21:21.881 --> 21:25.650
ONE WRONG MOVE
COULD RESULT IN MORE DEATHS.

21:31.590 --> 21:34.759
                WHOSE IS THAT?

21:51.043 --> 21:52.843
        YOU SAID
        YOU WOULDN'T HURT ME,
        SO LET ME GO.

21:52.845 --> 21:56.881
        THERE'S HARDLY ANYONE
        AROUND HERE. I SWEAR,
        I WON'T GO TO THE COPS.

21:56.883 --> 21:58.916
                BUT YOU SAID--
I CAN'T DO THAT.

21:58.918 --> 22:00.951
    ENOUGH!

22:00.953 --> 22:04.455
I'M NOT GOING TO LEAVE
A 16-YEAR-OLD GIRL ALONE

22:04.457 --> 22:06.590
ON THE SIDE OF THE ROAD.

22:06.592 --> 22:10.428
THAT WOULD BE BREAKING
MY PROMISE.

22:21.406 --> 22:24.608
        [ACCELERATING]

22:25.977 --> 22:27.778
        ANDY!

23:11.890 --> 23:12.957
[FIRES]

23:12.959 --> 23:14.759
            AAH!

23:19.431 --> 23:21.665
            OH, MY GOD.

23:21.667 --> 23:22.967
            ARE YOU OK?

23:22.969 --> 23:24.935
                    OHH!
    [FIRES]

23:24.937 --> 23:30.441
    [INDISTINCT GOSPEL SONG]

23:46.091 --> 23:49.660
OK, I KNOW AMELIA PORTER
HAD SURVIVAL SKILLS,

23:49.662 --> 23:51.996
BUT SHE MUST BE SOME SORT
OF A CRIMINAL MASTERMIND

23:51.998 --> 23:54.765
TO HAVE JUST VANISHED
WITHOUT A TRACE
FOR ALL THESE YEARS.

23:54.767 --> 23:57.735
    MAYBE SHE HAS A NEW VERSION
    OF BENTON HELPING HERE.

23:57.737 --> 24:01.205
    ACCORDING TO HER COUSIN'S
    STATEMENT, SHE DATED
    SEVERAL YOUNGER MEN

24:01.207 --> 24:02.740
    BEFORE BENTON,
    ALL IN THEIR EARLY 20s.

24:02.742 --> 24:06.977
        MAKES SENSE. YOUNGER MEN
        WERE EASIER TO SEDUCE
        AND CONTROL.

24:06.979 --> 24:08.212
    THE FARLAND CAR
    WAS JUST FOUND.

24:08.214 --> 24:11.215
    IT WAS INVOLVED
    IN A CRASH.

24:14.586 --> 24:15.986
IT'S AMAZING ANDY SURVIVED,

24:15.988 --> 24:17.822
CONSIDERING HOW LETHAL
BENTON HAS BEEN.

24:17.824 --> 24:20.458
        HE'S EITHER INCREDIBLY
        LUCKY OR HE WAS
        ALLOWED TO LIVE.

24:20.460 --> 24:24.895
    HOPEFULLY WE'LL BE ABLE
    TO GET SOME ANSWERS
    FROM HIM SOON.

24:24.897 --> 24:27.498
NO CELL PHONE OR I.D.
IN THE WOMAN'S PURSE.

24:27.500 --> 24:29.200
    WHAT DO YOU THINK?
    SHE ANOTHER HOSTAGE?

24:29.202 --> 24:31.035
        IT'S TOO MANY PEOPLE
        FOR BENTON TO CONTROL.

24:31.037 --> 24:33.838
        I THINK SHE WAS A GOOD
        SAMARITAN THAT STOPPED
        TO HELP WITH THE CRASH,

24:33.840 --> 24:37.808
WE SEARCHED A 100-YARD
PERIMETER. THERE'S NO SIGN
OF REBECCA FARLAND.

24:37.810 --> 24:40.110
    SO THERE'S A GOOD CHANCE
    HE HAS HER AND THAT
    SHE'S STILL ALIVE.

24:40.112 --> 24:44.248
    IF THAT'S THE CASE,
    WHAT'S HE HOLDING HER FOR?

25:09.574 --> 25:13.544
    ANDY. AGENTS CALLAHAN
    AND MORGAN, FBI.

25:13.546 --> 25:14.545
WHERE'S REBECCA?

25:14.547 --> 25:15.846
        WE'RE LOOKING FOR HER.

25:15.848 --> 25:18.716
CAN YOU TELL US
WHO SHOT YOU?

25:18.718 --> 25:20.584
    BENTON FARLAND.

25:20.586 --> 25:23.287
HE DIDN'T HAVE
HIS SEATBELT ON,

25:23.289 --> 25:25.723
AND I CRASHED THE CAR
ON PURPOSE.

25:25.725 --> 25:28.259
HE FIGURED OUT
I WAS TRYING TO KILL HIM.

25:28.261 --> 25:35.866
NO. NO, I WAS JUST PRETENDING,
TO PROTECT MY SISTER.

25:36.134 --> 25:37.301
BUT YOU HAVE TO FIND HER.

25:37.303 --> 25:41.906
        WE'RE DOING EVERYTHING
        WE CAN, BUT RIGHT NOW
        WE NEED YOU TO HELP US.

25:41.908 --> 25:48.145
UM, I TOLD HIM ABOUT
MY FRIEND'S VACATION CABIN.

25:48.147 --> 25:49.847
WE WERE HEADED THERE
BEFORE THE CRASH.

25:49.849 --> 25:54.251
IT'S THE YELLOW HOUSE
AT THE END
OF CANYON RIDGE LANE.

25:54.253 --> 25:56.587
PLEASE, YOU HAVE TO HURRY.

25:56.589 --> 25:58.289
SHE'S GONNA SAY SOMETHING
TO SET HIM OFF.

25:58.291 --> 26:02.192
    [INDISTINCT GOSPEL SONG]

26:28.054 --> 26:31.922
MORGAN AND KATE
JUST LEFT THE CABIN.
NO SIGN OF ANYONE.

26:31.924 --> 26:36.694
BENTON PROBABLY
CHANGED HIS PLAN
AFTER ANDY BETRAYED HIM.

26:36.696 --> 26:37.928
    WE JUST FOUND
    A BURNED-OUT CAR

26:37.930 --> 26:39.163
    ABOUT 50 MILES AWAY
    ON ROUTE 190.

26:39.165 --> 26:42.199
    HER DMV PHOTO MATCHES
    THE GOOD SAMARITAN.

26:47.639 --> 26:49.607
            WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

26:49.609 --> 26:51.675
NOTHING.

26:51.677 --> 26:53.143
I'M TIRED.

26:53.145 --> 26:55.913
AND COLD.

26:55.915 --> 26:58.882
WHERE ARE WE GOING,
ANYWAY?

26:58.884 --> 27:00.317
I JUST WANT TO KNOW
WHEN WE CAN REST.

27:00.319 --> 27:02.252
WE'VE BEEN WALKING FOR HOURS,

27:02.254 --> 27:03.220
            AND MY FOOT HURTS.

27:03.222 --> 27:07.658
WHEN WE GET THERE,
YOU'LL KNOW.

27:07.660 --> 27:10.127
        MY MOM USED TO SAY THAT.

27:11.162 --> 27:14.098
WELL, SHE GOT IT
FROM OUR MOM.

27:14.100 --> 27:16.934
THERE'S NO WAY
YOU COULD HAVE
REMEMBERED THAT.

27:16.936 --> 27:18.936
        YOU WERE TOO YOUNG.

27:18.938 --> 27:20.304
BUT I DO REMEMBER.

27:20.306 --> 27:22.706
AND I REMEMBER
WHEN I WAS LITTLE

27:22.708 --> 27:24.742
        AND YOU USED TO PUT ME
        ON YOUR SHOULDERS

27:24.744 --> 27:29.346
        SO THAT I COULD
        TOUCH THE STAR
        ON OUR CHRISTMAS TREE.

27:31.950 --> 27:35.219
YEAH, I DID DO THAT.

27:35.854 --> 27:39.857
HOW STUPID
DO YOU THINK I AM?

27:39.859 --> 27:44.328
THIS TRYING TO BOND
WITH ME AND BUILD RAPPORT
ISN'T GOING TO WORK.

27:44.330 --> 27:48.065
IT'S THE SAME CRAP
YOUR BROTHER PULLED.

27:49.801 --> 27:51.902
    YOU SHOT HIM, DIDN'T YOU?

27:51.904 --> 27:57.007
        YOU TOLD ME THAT ANDY
        DIED IN THE ACCIDENT,
        BUT YOU SHOT HIM!

27:57.009 --> 28:00.077
            IT'S ALL COMING
            BACK TO ME NOW.

28:00.079 --> 28:03.947
HE TRIED TO KILL ME...

28:03.949 --> 28:06.850
AND I HAD TO
PAY HIM BACK.

28:06.852 --> 28:10.354
IT'S ONLY FAIR...

28:10.356 --> 28:13.957
DON'T YOU THINK?

28:13.959 --> 28:16.994
WHEN SOMEONE BETRAYS YOU.

28:29.340 --> 28:31.241
        WE SHOULD CHECK THE...

28:31.243 --> 28:34.978
    THE GOOD NEW IS, THERE
    DON'T SEEM TO BE ANY
    HUMAN REMAINS INSIDE.

28:34.980 --> 28:37.047
Rossi: ANY IDEA WHY
HE STOPPED HERE?

28:37.049 --> 28:41.318
    Hotch: ANY HIKING TRAILS
    NEARBY THAT YOU KNOW OF,
    DETECTIVE?

28:41.320 --> 28:42.386
            NOT ANY MAJOR ONES.

28:42.388 --> 28:44.354
HEY, HOTCH,
TAKE A LOOK AT THIS.

28:44.356 --> 28:45.723
THESE TREADS LOOK REMARKABLY

28:45.725 --> 28:48.959
    LIKE THOSE
    FROM BENTON'S SHOES.

28:48.961 --> 28:50.027
WHAT'S OFF IN THAT DIRECTION?

28:50.029 --> 28:54.798
        THAT BRANCHES INTO
        OTHER PATHS THAT
        LEAD DOWN INTO A VALLEY.

28:54.800 --> 28:58.068
    THERE'S A SMATTERING
    OF SMALL FARMS AND HOUSES.

28:58.070 --> 28:59.303
BENTON CAME HERE ON PURPOSE.

28:59.305 --> 29:01.739
HE HAS A DESTINATION IN MIND.

29:01.741 --> 29:03.307
        IF IT'S NOT A PRISON
        CONNECTION,

29:03.309 --> 29:07.511
        IT MIGHT BE SOMEPLACE
        HE REMEMBERED
        FROM HIS CHILDHOOD.

29:07.513 --> 29:11.248
    I'LL FOLLOW UP WITH GARCIA.

29:17.822 --> 29:18.889
I HAVEN'T BETRAYED YOU.

29:18.891 --> 29:21.959
I HAVEN'T DONE ANYTHING
TO HURT YOU.

29:21.961 --> 29:24.528
    LOOK, I KNOW IT SOUNDS
    LIKE I'M TRYING TO PLAY YOU

29:24.530 --> 29:28.465
        BY SAYING THAT I DON'T
        THINK YOU'RE A BAD GUY,

29:28.467 --> 29:34.071
        YOU HAVE A HEART.
        YOU'RE JUST SNAKE-BITTEN
        LIKE YOU SAID.

29:34.073 --> 29:36.073
THAT I AM.

29:36.075 --> 29:42.179
        IF YOU LET ME GO,
        I SWEAR, I WON'T TELL
        ANYONE WHERE YOU ARE.

29:43.215 --> 29:48.552
YOU HAVEN'T BETRAYED ME YET,
BUT THE FIRST CHANCE YOU GET...

29:48.554 --> 29:50.053
    YOU WILL.

29:50.055 --> 29:52.089
                THAT'S NOT TRUE.

29:52.091 --> 29:53.891
I THINK IT IS.

29:53.893 --> 29:55.325
BUT JUST REMEMBER,

29:55.327 --> 29:58.462
I ALWAYS GET MY PAYBACK.

29:59.464 --> 30:02.099
    Man: MORNIN'!

30:02.101 --> 30:05.035
CAREFUL UP AHEAD.
IT LOOKS LIKE
PART OF THE PATH

30:05.037 --> 30:07.004
GOT WASHED OUT
WITH THE LAST STORM.

30:07.006 --> 30:08.372
    OK, WELL, THANKS
    FOR THE WARNING.

30:08.374 --> 30:10.440
HONEY, YOU LOOK
BLUE AS A POPSICLE.

30:10.442 --> 30:13.143
DIDN'T YOU BRING
YOUR JACKET?

30:13.145 --> 30:16.947
    YOU KNOW, I TOLD HER TO,
    BUT, TEENAGERS, RIGHT?

30:16.949 --> 30:19.316
        AIN'T THAT THE TRUTH.

30:19.318 --> 30:21.218
HAVE WE MET BEFORE?

30:21.220 --> 30:24.254
YOU LOOK SO FAMILIAR.

30:26.524 --> 30:28.125
                UM...

30:28.127 --> 30:33.564
WELL, YOU MUST REMIND ME
OF ONE OF MY DAUGHTER'S
CLASSMATES.

30:38.837 --> 30:40.003
        ALL RIGHT, THANKS
        FOR THE HEADS-UP.

30:40.005 --> 30:42.306
    YEAH. HAVE A GOOD 'UN.

30:42.308 --> 30:44.341
                MM-HMM.

30:51.182 --> 30:54.952
        ANDY SAID HIS UNCLE
        NEVER MENTIONED
        A JAILHOUSE CONNECTION.

30:54.954 --> 30:59.323
        BENTON MANAGED TO STAY
        A LONER BEHIND BARS.

30:59.325 --> 31:00.624
            HE NEVER AFFILIATED
            WITH ANY GROUPS

31:00.626 --> 31:02.192
            OR MADE FRIENDS WITH
            OTHER PRISONERS.

31:02.194 --> 31:05.462
        MOST PEOPLE HAVE
        AN INSTINCT
        FOR A SOCIAL CONNECTION.

31:05.464 --> 31:07.030
            MAYBE HE HAD ONE.

31:07.032 --> 31:11.001
        WELL, HE DIDN'T NEED
        ANY SOCIAL CONNECTIONS
        WHEN HE WAS IN PRISON

31:11.003 --> 31:12.936
            BECAUSE HE ALREADY
            HAD ONE.

31:12.938 --> 31:13.971
                AMELIA PORTER.

31:13.973 --> 31:15.205
EXCEPT SHE'S SOMEWHERE
IN CANADA

31:15.207 --> 31:16.506
SLEEPING AMONG
THE MOOSE AND BEARS.

31:16.508 --> 31:19.543
            PEOPLE ALSO HAVE
            A NATURAL INSTINCT
            TO RETURN HOME.

31:19.545 --> 31:20.544
YEAH, AND BENTON DID.

31:20.546 --> 31:23.614
    I'M GOING TO HAVE GARCIA
    LOOK FOR WOMEN IN THEIR 40s

31:23.616 --> 31:25.482
        WHO APPEARED IN THE AREA
        IN THE LAST 5 YEARS

31:25.484 --> 31:27.451
            WITH LITTLE OR NO
            HISTORY BEFORE THAT.

31:27.453 --> 31:29.653
TWO HIKERS IN THE MOUNTAINS
MAY HAVE SPOTTED THE SUSPECT

31:29.655 --> 31:32.522
AND HIS NIECE
ABOUT 30 MINUTES AGO.

31:48.072 --> 31:50.173
WHERE ARE WE?

31:50.175 --> 31:53.143
WHOSE HOUSE IS THIS?

32:28.279 --> 32:30.614
            WHAT THE HELL
            ARE YOU DOING HERE?

32:30.616 --> 32:33.383
HI, AMELIA.

32:38.123 --> 32:42.426
OF WHERE THE GOOD SAMARITAN'S
CAR WAS BURNED

32:42.428 --> 32:45.429
AND I FOUND NOT ONE,
BUT TWO WOMEN
WHO MATCH THE CRITERIA

32:45.431 --> 32:49.466
THE FIRST IS JANE APPLEBY.
SHE'S LIVED IN THE AREA
FOR 5 YEARS.

32:49.468 --> 32:53.403
SHE'S AN ORGANIC FARMER.
I GOT NOTHING ON HER
PRIOR TO 2009.

32:53.405 --> 32:58.375
SHE'S FROM WINNIPEG, CANADA.
SHE'S LIVED THERE FOR 4 YEARS.

32:58.377 --> 33:01.078
    BUT WHEN I LOOK HER UP
    PAST 2009,
    I CAN'T FIND ANYTHING.

33:01.080 --> 33:04.281
ALL RIGHT, DAVE,
YOU, KATE, AND REID
GO TO JANE APPLEBY'S HOUSE.

33:04.283 --> 33:07.184
THE REST OF US
WILL TAKE NATASHA BANKS.

33:07.186 --> 33:09.453
            HOW DID YOU FIND ME?

33:09.455 --> 33:12.990
        YOU WERE ALWAYS PREPARED
        FOR A DISASTER.

33:12.992 --> 33:16.126
        I NEVER FORGOT
        THE OLD SURVIVAL PLAN.

33:16.128 --> 33:18.161
    THAT WAS MY PLAN.
    YOU WERE NEVER A PART OF IT.

33:18.163 --> 33:22.432
        THEN YOU SHOULDN'T
        HAVE GOTTEN DRUNK
        AND TOLD ME ABOUT IT.

33:25.403 --> 33:27.471
                WHO'S THIS?

33:27.473 --> 33:29.306
        YOU DON'T RECOGNIZE HER?

33:29.308 --> 33:33.510
        IT'S REBECCA,
        MIRIAM'S DAUGHTER.

33:34.345 --> 33:38.548
    DOESN'T SHE LOOK
    JUST LIKE HER MOTHER?

33:40.752 --> 33:43.320
            OH, MY GOD.

33:43.322 --> 33:44.688
            YOU'RE SICK.

33:44.690 --> 33:45.756
        DID YOU KIDNAP HER?

33:45.758 --> 33:49.726
            DID I KIDNAP YOU?

33:49.728 --> 33:52.229
    NO.

33:53.464 --> 33:55.399
                SEE?

33:55.401 --> 33:58.335
            WE LIKE EACH OTHER.

33:59.537 --> 34:02.139
            WHAT DO YOU WANT?

34:06.344 --> 34:09.079
        CAN'T YOU GUESS?

34:14.452 --> 34:16.553
        YOU KNOW, SOMETHING'S
        BEEN BOTHERING ME.

34:16.554 --> 34:19.422
        IF BENTON ALWAYS
        INTENDED TO MEET AMELIA
        AFTER HIS RELEASE,

34:19.425 --> 34:24.360
            GOOD QUESTION.
            IT WASN'T JUST TO
            TAKE REVENGE ON DAD.

34:24.362 --> 34:28.498
THAT HE WENT TO AMELIA
PORTER'S OLD HOUSE.
LIKE HE WAS IMPROVISING.

34:28.500 --> 34:30.400
    OK, HERE'S
    A RADICAL THOUGHT.

34:30.402 --> 34:32.469
    WHAT IF AMELIA WASN'T
    THE DOMINANT ONE?

34:32.471 --> 34:34.304
    WHAT IF IT WAS REALLY
    BENTON?

34:34.306 --> 34:36.840
THE PROSECUTORS CALLED HER
A FEMME FATALE,

34:36.842 --> 34:40.543
            IT COULD HAVE BEEN
            THAT SHE HERSELF
            WAS IMMATURE.

34:40.545 --> 34:43.612
            HER PARENTS
            DESCRIBED HER
            AS SHY AND NAIVE.

34:43.614 --> 34:47.551
    SHE NEVER KILLED ANYONE
    BEFORE OR AFTER MIRIAM
    AS FAR AS WE KNOW.

34:47.553 --> 34:50.087
WHAT'S INTERESTING
IS AMELIA WAS 30 BACK THEN,

34:50.089 --> 34:52.556
AND HIS SISTER WAS ALMOST
THE SAME AGE AT 29.

34:52.558 --> 34:56.560
        THE FANTASY OF RAPING
        AND KILLING THE SISTER
        COULD HAVE BEEN HIS.

34:56.562 --> 35:01.098
WHEN BENTON TESTIFIED,
HE SAID THAT WHEN HIS
MOTHER DIED WHEN HE WAS 9,

35:01.100 --> 35:02.632
    MIRIAM BECAME
    HIS ENTIRE WORLD.

35:02.634 --> 35:08.772
IF SHE WAS ABSENT A LOT,
THAT WOULD'VE FUELED
BOTH DESIRE AND RAGE IN HIM.

35:08.774 --> 35:10.107
                    OHH!
            [SLAP]

35:10.109 --> 35:11.208
    12 YEARS!

35:11.210 --> 35:13.243
I SPENT 12 YEARS
IN THAT HELLHOLE

35:13.245 --> 35:15.178
WHILE YOU GOT OFF
SCOT-FREE.

35:15.180 --> 35:16.379
                STOP IT!

35:16.381 --> 35:18.715
                JUST STOP IT!

35:24.789 --> 35:29.159
I THINK THAT'S ENOUGH
PAYBACK.

35:30.495 --> 35:33.597
I'M SORRY, SWEETHEART.

35:33.599 --> 35:35.866
BUT YOU DESERVED IT.

35:35.868 --> 35:40.203
IT DOESN'T MEAN
I DON'T LOVE YOU.

35:42.473 --> 35:45.742
                [MOANS]

35:53.651 --> 35:55.552
THE OTHER REASON I'M HERE

35:55.554 --> 35:57.487
AND THE REASON WHY
I BROUGHT REBECCA,

35:57.489 --> 36:02.826
IS SO THAT WE COULD RELIVE
THE MOST EXCITING MOMENT
IN OUR LIVES.

36:02.828 --> 36:06.163
DOESN'T THAT SOUND LIKE FUN?

36:06.165 --> 36:08.765
                NO! NO!

36:14.372 --> 36:16.640
I ADMIT, SHE'S A LITTLE
YOUNG FOR MY TASTE,

36:16.642 --> 36:20.810
BUT SHE LOOKS SO MUCH
LIKE MIRIAM, DOESN'T SHE?

36:22.914 --> 36:24.681
GO AHEAD.

36:24.683 --> 36:28.685
DO IT.
YOU KNOW YOU WANT TO.

36:29.287 --> 36:30.754
            YOU CAN'T MAKE ME
            THIS TIME.

36:30.756 --> 36:34.791
OH, AMELIA,
STOP LYING TO YOURSELF.

36:34.793 --> 36:37.194
YOU LOVED IT.
IT WAS GLORIOUS.

36:37.196 --> 36:40.697
            I WAS HIGH.
            I WAS OUT OF MY MIND
            SEEING THINGS.

36:40.699 --> 36:43.667
YOU TOUCHED GOD
IN THAT MOMENT.

36:43.669 --> 36:46.536
        WE MURDERED YOUR SISTER.

36:46.538 --> 36:47.604
            FBI!

36:47.606 --> 36:48.705
    DROP THE WEAPON!

36:48.707 --> 36:51.208
        YOU'RE NOT TAKING ME
        WITH YOU.

36:51.210 --> 36:54.277
            HE'S CRAZY.
            HE TRIED TO FORCE ME
            TO HURT HER.

36:54.279 --> 36:56.880
        THIS COMING FROM THE
        WOMAN WHO KILLED MIRIAM?

36:56.882 --> 37:01.418
WE'VE BEEN LOOKING FOR YOU
FOR 12 YEARS, AMELIA.

37:01.420 --> 37:03.720
        Amelia: IT WAS HIM.
        IT WAS ALWAYS HIM.

37:03.722 --> 37:05.455
WHY DID YOU RUN?

37:05.457 --> 37:09.659
        WHO WOULD BELIEVE ME
        OVER A 17-YEAR-OLD BOY?

37:09.661 --> 37:11.928
PUT THE GUN DOWN.
AMELIA'S THE ONE WE WANT.

37:11.930 --> 37:16.533
    SHE'S THE ONE WE'RE AFTER,
    AND YOU LED US TO HER.

37:16.535 --> 37:18.768
YOUR NEPHEW ANDY EXPLAINED HOW
EVERYTHING HAPPENED, BENTON.

37:18.770 --> 37:21.304
WE KNOW NONE OF THIS
WAS YOUR FAULT.

37:21.306 --> 37:22.606
    HE'S ALIVE?

37:22.608 --> 37:24.874
HE'S IN THE HOSPITAL.

37:24.876 --> 37:25.875
                [SOBBING]

37:25.877 --> 37:26.776
    THANK GOD.

37:26.778 --> 37:29.446
LET HER GO, BENTON.

37:39.323 --> 37:41.891
                [GASPING]

37:46.664 --> 37:49.899
    ♪ O, LORD, REMEMBER ME ♪

37:49.901 --> 37:52.736
    ♪ REMEMBER ME ♪

37:52.738 --> 37:56.706
    ♪ O LORD, REMEMBER ME ♪

37:56.708 --> 37:58.908
        ♪ REMEMBER ME ♪

37:58.910 --> 38:02.846
    ♪ WHEN THESE CHAINS
    GET BROKEN ♪

38:02.848 --> 38:06.449
    ♪ SET MY BODY FREE ♪

38:06.451 --> 38:09.919
    ♪ O LORD, REMEMBER ME ♪

38:09.921 --> 38:12.589
    Kate: "THE SOUL THAT HAS
    CONCEIVED ONE WICKEDNESS

38:12.591 --> 38:14.658
        CAN NURSE NO GOOD
        THEREAFTER."

38:14.660 --> 38:17.360
♪ ...I CALL YOUR NAME ♪

38:17.362 --> 38:19.663
    ♪ I CALL YOUR NAME ♪

38:19.665 --> 38:24.834
    ♪ DAYS GET LONG,
    I CALL YOUR NAME ♪

38:24.836 --> 38:27.704
♪ I CALL YOUR NAME ♪

38:27.706 --> 38:30.507
    ♪ DAYS GET LONG ♪

38:30.509 --> 38:34.477
♪ CAN'T SEE RIGHT FROM WRONG ♪

38:34.479 --> 38:37.947
    ♪ O LORD, I CALL YOUR NAME ♪

38:37.949 --> 38:40.583
        ♪ I CALL YOUR NAME... ♪

38:40.585 --> 38:44.921
    [JAZZ PLAYING]

38:45.523 --> 38:51.728
♪ YOU KNOW YOU WANT IT, BABY ♪

38:51.730 --> 38:56.366
    ♪ AND, OH, YOU REALLY DO ♪

38:56.368 --> 39:02.906
    ♪ AH, YOU KNOW
    YOU CAN'T RESIST ME ♪

39:02.908 --> 39:11.348
    ♪ SO, COME ON BABY,
    KISS ME ♪

39:18.757 --> 39:21.624
            SHE'S GREAT.
            YOU COULD DO WORSE.

39:21.626 --> 39:24.661
            SO, WHEN ARE YOU
            GOING TO
            INTRODUCE YOURSELF?

39:24.663 --> 39:26.863
AH, I DON'T KNOW, AARON.
I'M NOT GONNA PLAN,

39:26.865 --> 39:28.064
I'M JUST GONNA
GO WITH THE FLOW

39:28.066 --> 39:29.833
AND SEE WHAT
OPPORTUNITIES ARISE.

39:29.835 --> 39:31.835
 AND I SUGGEST
 YOU DO THE SAME.

39:31.837 --> 39:32.869
            I'M HERE, AREN'T I?

39:32.871 --> 39:34.771
YES. THAT'S A GREAT START.

39:34.773 --> 39:39.376
    UM, THANKS FOR
    THE BOTTLE OF CHAMPAGNE.

39:39.378 --> 39:41.745
BARTENDER TOLD ME
YOU SENT IT.

39:41.747 --> 39:44.647
        SO MUCH FOR BEING
        A SECRET ADMIRER.

39:44.649 --> 39:45.548
            [CHUCKLES]

39:45.550 --> 39:47.117
I'M CELINE DESTIN.

39:47.119 --> 39:49.085
THIS IS MY FRIEND
AUDREY HANSEN.

39:49.087 --> 39:51.788
    DAVID ROSSI,
    AND MY FRIEND
    AARON HOTCHNER.

39:51.790 --> 39:54.824
        HI. HOW DO YOU DO?
        NICE TO MEET YOU.

39:54.826 --> 39:56.793
                    HI.
            HI, HOW ARE YOU?

39:57.928 --> 40:01.631
STRONG, SILENT TYPES.

40:01.633 --> 40:02.932
INTELLIGENT.

40:02.934 --> 40:04.567
HONEST EYES.

40:04.569 --> 40:06.836
SO YOU'RE NOT POLITICIANS.

40:06.838 --> 40:08.705
    [BOTH LAUGH]

40:08.707 --> 40:09.739
        FBI.

40:09.741 --> 40:13.810
    WOW. YOU TWO
    COULD BE PROFILERS.

40:13.812 --> 40:15.145
WELL, AUDREY PRACTICALLY IS.

40:15.147 --> 40:16.880
I MEAN, SHE'S IN MARKETING.

40:16.882 --> 40:18.882
SHE JUST MOVED HERE
FROM SAN DIEGO.

40:18.884 --> 40:21.050
    THEN WELCOME
    TO OUR FAIR CITY.

40:21.052 --> 40:23.086
    AND WOULD YOU LADIES
    CARE TO JOIN US?

40:23.088 --> 40:25.088
I WISH I COULD.
I HAVE TO GET BACK.

40:25.090 --> 40:27.590
 I'LL BE OFF AT 10:00,
 THOUGHT.

40:27.592 --> 40:28.992
        THEN I'LL BE WAITING.

40:28.994 --> 40:31.694
ALL RIGHT.

40:31.696 --> 40:33.730
    IF YOU DON'T MIND...

40:33.732 --> 40:37.167
    I'M GOING TO AMBLE
    UP TO THE BAR
    FOR ANOTHER DRINK,

40:37.169 --> 40:39.869
BUT, AUDREY, PLEASE,

40:39.871 --> 40:41.805
    HAVE A SEAT.

40:41.807 --> 40:45.875
AND, UM, MY FRIEND
IS KNOWN TO BE

40:45.877 --> 40:50.947
AN EXCELLENT TOUR GUIDE.

40:51.982 --> 40:52.916
                    SORRY.

40:52.918 --> 40:57.053
        [LAUGHS]

40:58.456 --> 41:00.156
LET ME GUESS.

41:00.158 --> 41:01.491
WINGMAN?

41:01.493 --> 41:06.062
MM. MORE LIKE THE SIDEKICK
WHO CAN'T CARRY A TUNE.

41:06.064 --> 41:12.602
    ♪ THE BEST UPPER SETS
        DO IT ♪

41:12.604 --> 41:17.106
    ♪ LITUANIANS
    AND LETTS DO IT ♪

41:17.108 --> 41:18.842
SO IS HE A HEARTBREAKER?

41:18.844 --> 41:21.478
    WELL, FULL DISCLOSURE,
    HE HAS BEEN MARRIED 3 TIMES,

41:21.480 --> 41:25.782
        BUT...HE'S A SOLID
        AS THEY COME
        AND HE'S LEARNING.

41:25.784 --> 41:27.984
WELL, GOOD. THAT'S GOOD.

41:27.986 --> 41:29.185
                    AND HER?

41:29.187 --> 41:33.656
IF HE TREATS HER RIGHT,
SHE'S A DREAM.

41:33.658 --> 41:35.058
SO TELL ME SOMETHING.

41:35.060 --> 41:37.594
ARE YOU REALLY
AN EXCELLENT TOUR GUIDE?

41:37.596 --> 41:38.528
[CHUCKLES]

41:38.530 --> 41:41.064
                I'VE BEEN TOLD
                I'M PRETTY GOOD.

41:41.066 --> 41:41.998
                    YEAH.
    OH.

41:42.000 --> 41:43.233
YOU DON'T SAY.

41:43.235 --> 41:44.901
        [BOTH LAUGH]

41:44.903 --> 41:47.804
SO IF YOU WERE TO TAKE ME
ON A TOUR,

41:47.806 --> 41:52.141
    WELL, MOST PEOPLE
    WOULD START WITH
    THE OBVIOUS, THE MONUMENTS,

41:52.143 --> 41:55.645
        BUT THERE'S SOME
        LESSER-KNOWN PLACES
        THAT ARE VERY NICE.

41:55.647 --> 42:01.251
        THE, UH, MOONGATE GARDEN
        AT THE SMITHSONIAN
        IS REALLY BEAUTIFUL,

42:01.253 --> 42:03.119
        ESPECIALLY AT SUNSET.

42:03.121 --> 42:06.189
        I'VE GOT A FEW THINGS
        UP MY SLEEVE.

42:06.191 --> 42:09.659
    [CELINE'S SONG ENDS]

